caption: Had a couple of beers and some nachos before the Orioles game, sat at one of the tables on Eutaw street which was great as it was such a nice day. Our server was great and you get they start you off with a complimentary basket of their crab seasoning chips which were very good. The nachos were good but not too much wrong that you can do to nachos, wish I would have ordered other food options but wasn’t that hungry. Overall it was a really good experience.

Stopped here for a late lunch on Thursday. I liked the way the place was decorated. There was hardly anyone there so we sat at the bar. Plenty of people working and not many customers.  I ordered a beer and they said it would be a minute as they had to retap it. Fast forward 25 minutes and still no beer. I finally just asked for something else as they seemed as if they couldn’t care less.  We got  our food and it was wrong. The bar tender just shrugged it off and said they’ve been making mistakes back there all day. I decided to just go with it and get the hell out of there. They still charged us for what we didn’t get but again I didn’t want to spend another minute in there so I paid it and left. The manager was there the whole time too, what a joke.

Stay away from this dump, TERRIBLE experience! Sat at the bar with friends, the server avoided eye contact with us so our wait time was exceptionally long.  When the bill came, I didn't  leave a tip because of the terrible service.  When I checked my bannk statement, I saw that Dempseys took it upon themselves to add a $20.00 tip.  I emailed Dempseys and was refunded the 20 dollars and was offered a free return visit, which I did not accept. I recommend eating outside the ballpark!
The atmosphere and ambiance was tops. The service and food was on point. Very clean environment and parking is validated.

Was sitting at a table with a friend before the Ravens Titans game. Had a couple of beers and an appetizer. Decided to move to the bar when a pair of seats opened up. 5 minutes at bar and the bartender is giving my friend a hard time because he wasn't drinking. "We've got family's to feed. There's customers that would like to sit here and your not drinking". I don't recommend spending any of your $ at this RUDE establishment!
Love the atmosphere
Fantastic food, super friendly employees, regularly great ambience. They charge fair pricing and the food quality is excellent. Kudos.

Loved it! Services was great!!! We had previously gone to Pickles Pub and the service was awful so it was so refreshing how amazing the staff was here. Food was great! Maybe yes a little pricey but hey may as well go for it when you know your getting great food and great service. Such a great location too!
Great wedding reception
Really amazing
The food was great. Robin provided Excellent Service!!!
Just spent 20 minutes at the bar. Left because no one was behind the bar, or asked for a order or even greeted us. So disappointed
Tasty food but should not give customers a new disposable, plastic cup after every refill. They should be more environment-conscious.
It was just a cool place to be

Only 2 people working. Took forever to get a menu. I got my food before I even got a drink. Couldnt find anyone to get a refill and had to track someone down to get my check. The crab dip and pretzels were amazing

My husband and I attended the game on September 21st, I left my husband choose where we would eat and he chose your establishment and I can honestly say we are so glad we ate there we had the Camden bird sandwich and omg was that good, beside the food the service was great and my husband wanted me to mention sous chef Ken he was very conscientious about the service of the customers and was very professional, just a super nice guy and I will be happy to say we will return again
The atmosphere is awesome. The smell of beer, hot dogs, popcorn, and pretzels. I love the sound of the crack of the bat.

I have eaten at Dempsey's several times in the past and enjoyed it very much.  However this year I was very dissappointed in the menu selection.  It was very limited.  If this menu remains the same I don't think I will go there again.
Horrid service. Nobody here of course because team stinks, but STILL couldn't get served at the bar. RUDE. Skip this place.

Expensive! Two beers served in plastic cups and an order of wings was 40.00 with tip. The place was dead on the Friday I was here, but granted they must get more traffic during games. The beers, which are contract brewed by Heavy Seas, were nothing to write home about. The wings were very good. Only four original beers on tap, so not exactly a beer drinkers paradise, more like a gimmick to keep up with the explosion of breweries in and around the city. Wouldn't make a special trip here unless you are already here to watch a game.
Poor service, cold food, at 14 bucks for a burger, I would expect better.  One timer for me.
Went there on a game day. Place wasn’t even crowded and we sat at the bar for roughly > 15 minutes without getting acknowledged before we left. Was really looking forward to trying this place too.

I gave a 3 star, because the food was just okay. We got the vrap dip as an appetizer and I thought it could have had more old bay in it. My wife and I got the crab cake and though I liked the sauce they put on it, the crabcake had a lot of filler in it. We will go back but we will definitely be trying something else to eat.
Great fast service
Had lunch at Dempsey's today.  The food was really good, and that Pulled Pork Sandwich was perfection!!  Service was fast, which was good, because we had to go back to work.  Great experience.

It was clean and food was okay. The service however was really bad and everything took FOREVER. Everyone seemed stressed and the restaurant just looked like it was ran poorly (someone literally quit while we were there). My water was never filled when it was empty I had to ask a few times for that and any napkins. If you’re thinking you’re going to pay extra for AC forget it because there was none. It was so hot in there , you might as well eat for cheaper at a different stand outside or in the stadium.

Based on our experience this past Saturday 3 stars is somewhat generous. We put our names in and they sent us a test text message to reach us  When our table was ready. We then told them we would be sitting in the bar. It was going to be a 45 minute wait and that was fine with us.  About 40 minutes in I went to check and see where we were on the list and they told me that they were no longer allowed to use the text message system and that they had already called R name at the front door. I said but we were in the bar and she said the manager told her not to go in the bar. They eventually found us a table and the air conditioning was not working and there are no ceiling fans in the main dining Room. Once we were seated our server was actually fantastic and got our food and drinks very quickly. The food itself was very good. But there were no sides and I'm not sure if there were supposed to be or not at that point we were going to be late for the game.  I am not sure if it is always like this however was very disappointing when we were told that a manager decided not to make sure that we could hear our name be called and not to use the text message system. I can't imagine why that would be the case.
Great food and the proportion was huge so it was worth the money. Our server was fantastic.
Great lunch!
Do not get the chicken tenders, probably the worst I've had.. poor taste, difficult to eat and pull apart, and too pricey to boot. Go elsewhere.
Not worth the hype. The wait staff is great, decent beer and the food is meh. The inside is nice, kind of an upscale bar.

We've been going there for years and always had great food and service. Last year but mainly this year the service and food has not been good at all.  This past week we gave it another try and decided we wont be eating there anymore.  We ordered wings well done and when they came out there weren't well done.  When we mentioned it to the waitress she offered to send the chef out so we could tell him.  He never came out and they didnt offer to replace them or remove from bill. Sorry Dempsey we're done.

First of all, we were lured in by one of the guys outside the park. He told us they had an amazing free (free?) brunch. Well, the brunch is $38. Nowhere near free. We decided to stay anyway and order off the menu. My husband ordered the cheese steak sandwich. He's pretty sure they used cheese whiz for the sandwich. The vegetables were undercooked and they served what looked like a pickle on the side but is actually a cucumber. I ordered honey mustard with my chicken and it didn't come out until the end of the meal. The waitress wasn't friendly, maybe having a bad day but it made the overall experience kind of suck. Overpriced and overrated. Do not recommend.

Overpriced for an establishment that pre-cooks many items. There have been several times when I have asked for something made a particular way or with one ingredient removed and I have been told its pre-made. The food is hit or miss. This week the food may taste a lot better than last week. The burgers are good. But you can spend close to $10 adding ingredients to the "build your own". Cheese is $2. Seems a bit absurd.
Excellent food adjacent to Camden Yards.
Great appetizers
A fun place at the Yard.
The best !!! Period!!!

We were at Camden Yards for an unplanned doubleheader.  We figured iF we missed the first pitch of the first game, not a biggie.  WELL!  We got timely service, good food, and a nice visit.  Prices are not unreasonable.  The service was good.  Neat atmosphere.  We will probably go again.  the tables are not too close together.  Menu not big, but good choices.  And we made it to our seats for the first pitch.
Good food, brisk service, and a great place for a private party
Good service good food. Pregame meal
Attended a private party.  The food and service was excellent.
Place was nice and clean server was OK food taste regular I gave a three because for the kind of food they prepare is over price. Too pricey for wings and sub.
Very dry!
We love it here. We stop every time we take a trip to Virginia. The bacon on a stick is a must-have! The wait staff is so friendly and the food is always great.
Bacon on a stick!!!
Great food and view
Good beer, and happy hour!
Always a fun place to hangout. Delicious food, good beer, great staff, and surrounded by baseball history!
Great lunch.
Burger was great.   Service left something to be desired.  Got tired of having to keep asking for things repeatedly.
Cool layed back
Usually Dempsey's is great and we enjoy it a lot. Tonight though we waited over an hour after ordering and never even got our appitizer. We ended up just leaving with two starving kids and parents.

This was my first time here. It was a quiet day as this restaurant is tied to Camden Yard and it is very cold. The food was very good and they have a wide selection of lunch items to pick from. Reasonable priced given the quality and quantity of food. 4 people had a very nice lunch with appetizer for $80.
Awesome food with perfect hospitality
Favorite go to place in Baltimore. Pub in the Orioles stadium.
Congested, not many smiles... Wish they were open after the game.
Great place to go before the game!!!  Both the food and staff were terrific!!!
A great place to grab a beer before watching the Orioles!

At best its average here. The prices are more expensive than the offerings should allow.  I understand game day pricing is meant to gouge the consumer, which is still sad, but the pedestrian offerings should have prices well below their current rates.
First time there for lunch place was clean and the food was delicious.my waiter Michael was great.
No decaf  coffee
Wonderful, polite, attentive staff. Food was great.

Can't beat the view unless you go to the club area on the top floor. No baseball now but it is always a great view into Camden Yards. The hamburgers are also terrific. That is all I order when I eat there.
Good food. Expensive prices.
Great  Customer  Service
Servers are RUDE and take their sweet time this is includes managment
Better with a beer

Awful experience! The service was extremely slow. It took 10 minutes for our drinks. The food was average . It took 38 minutes for our food to be delivered . We were late returning to our class because this place had no sense of urgency. I would definitely NOT recommend this place and I will not return.
Stopped in before game, busy but we were able to get a seat at the bar. Beer choices were great, food and service good. Pretty reasonably priced for inside ballpark.
Fun place to go before or during the baseball game.
Can't really even rate the place because we were unable to get a table. They were completely unprepared for a doubleheader I guess!!
Great bar great place sports bar inside the Orioles stadium nice place to spend some time
Great food along with great music.
Great food!

We always made a point to go to Dempseys prior to O's games, but was extremely disappointed with the $100 bill for my husband and 4 year old and myself and awful service this Sunday's afternoon game. We had to ask for drink refills,  ask for napkins and silverware and everyone's food was served and I had to ask for mine. Someone needs to add restaurant competition so that is not the only choice or they need to have better service.  Respectfully,
Little bit of a long wait for food. Food is good but on the expensive side.
Excellent food, inexperienced waitress. She needed several reminders.
Very expensive and food quality was average!

We sat at the bar for about 25 minutes, without a bartender coming over to us. Granted it was super busy, however there were 3 or 4 groups of people that arrived after us, were served and left before the bartender even acknowledge our section of the bar. We were a group of 4, as well, and so it wasn't like we weren't noticable. The food, however, is delicious, so it still earns 4 stars overall.
Meh. Nothing special. The craft beers were average. The Cosmo was terrible.
cool
Expensive but worth it
You'll love it if your an O's Fan!
Great staff and top notch happy hour selections for food and drink
Great food service and atmosphere
Average sandwiches priced too high and fries are extra
Crab Cake sandwich was one the best I've had in the city and great atmosphere being right by the Oriole's stadium!
I just wanted a hot dog.
Good place to get out of the weather and get a good bite to eat.
Good Burgers, good atmosphere

Me and my wife were some of the first customers in the door for a Sunday afternoon game at Orioles Park. Although there were almost no tables taken, our host walked us past a lot of good tables and sat us right next to the kitchen, which we quickly realized was the worst table in the building. the constant rush of servers and busboys created a draft, and we asked to be relocated. They moved us to a table two spots up. The table was disgusting, not cleaned, to the point where I put a few napkins down over the top. I ordered their house burger, and my wife ordered a pulled pork sandwich, with a house salad with ranch instead of coleslaw. Pretty simple, right? After a moderate wait, our order arrived, to my wife's disappointment. They brought her a pulled pork sandwich with no bun, and a salad with no ranch. They also brought her the coleslaw she hates, and no house chips, which come with every sandwich. The server apologized and fixed the screw-up, but we were one of only two parties in his section at the time. The menu also says the chips are old bay flavored, but the chips we got were plain. The only reason why this place gets two stars instead of one is the burger was pretty good and my wife says the pulled pork wasn't bad, after she got her bun. The pricing was what I expected from a bar and grill located inside of a ballpark. Will not return.

Beer costs the same inside Dempsey's as it does outside but is 1/2 the size, nice job Rick.  Our waiter last night (Patrick), after I specified that I didn't want our meal delivered too close to our appetizer came within seconds of our our staring the appetizer.  Then, he put other table's orders in under our table number, so every few minutes a food server would show up and try to give us somebody else's food.  To top it off,  the lights over our area kept flashing on and off making our dinner somewhat nuts.  Needless to say Rick, we won't be back, we'll be heading over to Boog's place.
Great game day atmosphere, very attentive wait staff
Love this pub the bacon on a stick is amazing. A great place to go before the Oriole game!
Not a bad place open to the public without going into the stadium.

Just left there for lunch.  Food was good but the service was definitely lacking.  It took forever for my food order to be taken and I did not see my server again until I was finished.  I cracked open a bottle of water that I had in my briefcase and refilled my glass.  When she finally came back she apologized for the service and offered to refill my drink.  I said no thanks and asked for the check.  12 - 15 minutes she returned with my check.  I immediately gave her credit card so that I would not have to wait another 10 minutes for her come back.  The sad part about this experience was that the restaurant wasn't even half-full.
Pretty damn good!
Great place to grab a quick lunch when downtown
Great place e
Good food; high prices.

Pretty average for a sports bar. Because it is attached to Camden Yards they can get away with higher prices than your average restaurant but the quality is fairly on par. They are a brewery also, which is a plus, but the quality of the brews so far is pretty standard and they havnt gotten to the point where they expiriment with new flavors.
The Wings were good and the happy hour price was good too.

I was pretty much starving when we stumbled into Dempsey's after a heartbreaking Ravens game.  The staff was so gracious and happy even though they were getting slammed by sports fans on their way out of the area.  The service was fast and the food was delicious.  The leftovers were even great when I ate them out of my fridge the next day.
Good food, reaches seating capacity quickly on game days.
The burgers are tasty.
We we're at Dempsey's for a private event and it couldn't have been any nicer.
Food was ok. Service was good. House beers were lacking but some of the other beers were good. Great view of the stadium.
Serve could use considerable improvment, BBQ pulled pork sandwich is nothing to write home about, but the sweet potato tots were great!
Great service from Gabby, Jim and staff..excellent food

Game day, first group of people going in, you think the staff would be fresh and ready - Not! Rude, argumentative and eyes rolling from the waitress. My family and I were excited for the afternoon game but quickly realized we should have eaten outside. Overpriced, the food was average and if you substitute, you are charged greatly no matter how small. Waitress failed to tell us this info and the menu does not say either and I dare not to question the waitress. It took 3 sandwiches to get mine right and the manager said I would not be charged but I was with this statement under my charge "Do not serve food". We frequently attend games and this was our first and last time to go to this so called establishment.
Sucked
Loved the bacon on a stick.
Not much got food service ok food ok
Your watress named tim is not very good. He didn't ask how the food was. Didn't bring us our drank u til another man did. He messed up the food orders.
Slow service but delicious sweet potato tater tots.  Cherry lemonade wasn't worth $9. Great location.
Good food. Tuna bites are delish! Great atmosphere!
Fun, friendly place.  Beware of the tuna though!
Service was slow.  Good atmosphere.
Don't ask for a substitution. Pleasant enough. Not crowded during lunch, which is nice.
Great location, great food, and great atmosphere overall

First time eating here, was surprised how fast we got in and seated. Got there about an hour and a half before game time. Had the cheesesteak w/ egg, homemade chips and their 1983 brew. Everything was good. Four dudes each ordering a meal and a beer was 87.00. Left a 15.00 tip. Thought it wasn't bad for the Yard.
Love the feel of being in the Yard and being able to eat great food
Standing just by the entrance:  looking at six (6) empty tables, and a line of more than 30 people waiting semi-patiently.  It's been 30+ minutes since I checked in... What's wrong with this picture?
Fun pub style restaurant built into the stadium

If you time it right, you may just get a visit from the man himself, Rick Dempsey.  We were lucky enough to time it right and then during a second visit, he spent time talking with our son about little league baseball.  Genuine man, good eats, and delicious drinks in beautiful Oriole Park at Camden Yards.  What could be better than baseball, living history, and beer?
Walked in,  waited 10 minutes with no service and left.  No wonder there were so few people there.

We stopped in after a game on Memorial day and it was very good.  The staff was extremely nice and cleaned off a table for us so we didn't have to wait long at all. The food was very good and beer was ice cold!!

This is a good establishment. To me it is nice to break up some innings and come to this restaurant to enjoy a few drinks and a meal. The staff is friendly and there are a lot of TVs so you can keep watching and listening to the game.  For an in-stadium restaurant, this place is good. The food won't be the best in Baltimore but it will be the best you can find in the stadium.  I'll go back here again.

Nice atmosphere and good service. The free parking voucher was also nice.  The beer was just okay I thought.  The emphasis was on burgers, so I ordered one with an egg. The patty was very thin, overcooked, and flavorless. The egg yolk was also cooked through.  Why put an egg on a hamburger without a runny yolk?

Four different entrees were ordered.  Quesadillas, Chicken Wings w/Thai sauce, Bacon and Egg Cheese Burger and  Chicken Tenderloins.  Everything was great with exception of chicken tenderloins.  They were extremely dry.  Waiter Tim was FABULOUS!
AWESOME place

I really don't want to give any stars because we never got our food after an hour wait and there was barely anybody in there... We ended up leaving... and so did many other people waiting for their food
See yelp reviews
Baseball and beer -- do you need more?

Service was great , & can't beat the location:) i wasn't crazy about my nachos, tho...They were kinda drowning in some kind of cheese sauce that I didn't like... Would have preferred to have had just cheddar, like, real cheddar, instead. Real food tastes better!  Honey liked his sandwich, tho, and they were very nice to our service puppy - brought water for her and us right away :)
Service was slow. We had to ask to be served and then a beverage was forgotten. Food was ok for a ball park.

Nice beer list for those looking for something different. We went on a Sunday night, moderately busy due to the conference in town, and had issues with service. Our wait staff was friendly but one member in our party got served the incorrect order. The waitress apologized and returned it to the kitchen for a new plate, but nothing ever came back. We had to grab someone after roughly 20-30 minutes. Food did eventually arrive. Typical bar/pub. Dimly lit, wood finish, and a focus on drinks and social as opposed to food. Not to knock the food though. No one I was with complained.
Nice food and atmosphere both during games and during down time.
Fine Brews
Nice selection of beers and good pub food.  Always a go to before Raven's and O's games
Not busy but service was very slow, food was okay, nothing exciting.

It's meant for baseball. Plain and simple. It's appeal is the stadium and the radio shows it hosts. Food is just ok and focuses on too many deep fried type options. It's OK to have a baseball sports bar that doesn't kill it's patrons with super fat foods. Beer is nothing special nor is it like the cheap bars nearby. Their own pubbrews are nothing special but they should just focus on showcasing more Maryland brews like flying dog, heavy seas, jailbreak, etc.
Excellent selection of in house brewed beer. The food is amazing! Can't go wrong with this place!
That Bacon was Great.  Dugout Cheese Steak with an egg, onions and peppers hit the spot.
Great Beers!!!

Wow. Me and my son (6) come from North Carolina for his first game (a win) and the next day stop into Dempsey's. The Manager was awesome and gave my son some memorabilia and then brings me his cell phone and I get to talk to a childhood hero of mine Rick Dempsey. What an honor. I highly recommend this place. Cool pictures, nice people and great food with view of Camden Yards. First class treatment. Thanks
Good sports atmosphere.

Oh boy... We came to this place on a whim, not expecting much. Expectations... Not exceeded. All of the staff seemed like they had just smoked a mile high stack of doobs. No napkins, utensils, or water were provided. The server came out with our food and called our burger a crab cake... Wuuuuuut. And then he seemed really upset when I questioned him. He turned his back to us and started watching tv for a full two minutes before dragging his knuckles back to the kitchen. I'm questioning my rating of two stars at this moment. Maybe one is more appropriate. Our waitress was very nice, to be fair, but it also seemed like she may have been on a staycation on Mars courtesy of Mary Jane & Company. We could have just been really unlucky, but I don't think I would come back here given the opportunity. There are waaaaay better options within walking distance and something called the Charm City Circulator. Price-wise, also not worth it. You could get an equivalent meal for 50% or less. Bottom line... Don't "eat" here.
Great spinach artichoke dip, enough as dinner for two. Craft beer was ok.
Great meal good atmosphere
Pretty decent bar place. The service could be a little faster.

Great atmosphere and an amazing view of the baseball stadium. You can even walk through part of the stadium on Eutaw Street. Friendly staff and great food. My favorite is the Jack Daniel's Burger with sweet potato tots. Awesome place to be on game and non-game days!

I was visiting from out of town and happened to walk past the pub during the day.  I saw they had a happy hour so I decided to get my group that I was traveling with to come back in the afternoon.  It was a non game day so there may have been 20 customers in the whole place.  We were seated outside and basically our server never came to our table after about 15 minutes.  The manager actually took our drink order and then disappeared.  The server showed up about 5 minutes later to take our drink order even though the manager already took it.  I could really go on about how bad the service was.  When we finally got our drinks one was wrong but we did not complain.  On the next order we asked for a glass and the server never came back.  I had to go inside and get a glass from the bar.  The food was pretty good except for a couple of chicken wings that were under cooked.  I was really excited about this place because of the atmosphere but had to apologize to my group for making the suggestion to eat here.  I am not sure how this place could even operate if it was a game day.  Maybe the A-team is not there on non game days.  Very disappointing.
Beer was sub par, food was great.  Gets SUPER crowded on game days

Waited over an hour to be seated because we were a party of 7. The crazy thing is that they had over 10 open tables for over 30 minutes! Finally, after about 65 minutes and talking to them four times, they pushed two tables together. Unless you have about 4 hours to wait, don't bother coming here. Btw, the food was mediocre at best as well.
The Bolognapeppercorn was alright.
I love this place game day or any day the food is great and the service is wonderful, love the bacon on the stick.

Ordered the Sweet and Spicy Wagyu burger for 14 dollars. When it first came out, it was just a plain burger with just pickles and lettuce. I told them I ordered the Wagyu Burger from the menu with pineapple relish, bacon, arugula, pepper jack, and teriyaki glaze. They took it back to the kitchen and just threw some pineapple and sauce on it. When it came back out, it still had no cheese or bacon. The waitress came by and took it back. By the time they remade it for me, both of my friends had finished eating. It was also well done when I asked for medium.  When the checks came, my buddy had a $10 off card. She brought the checks and forgot to apply the $10 card so she had to redo the checks.  The only pro was the beer brewed onsite and the O's game.

I have been going there since it opened! It is great place for the family! A great place for a date! A great place for a social event! Oh did I mention it is a wonderful place on game day too! The food? Out of this world! I have become a semi regular especially during the off-season or when the Orioles are not in town! This restaurant has a breathtaking view of the field, and the architecture is a thing of beauty! The service is always outstanding, and the bathrooms are always clean! Plus, there is validated parking! Try the happy hour especially when the team is out of town and a great place to watch a road game. Love it! We recently had a social for our professional group and let's just say it was a hit! We ended up selling tickets in a block for the upcoming Yankees game with great seats outside of Dempsey's. My favorites are the sweet potato tots, the Old Bay fries, the fish tacos, burgers, wings, pizza and the pulled pork! Yep I have hit the menu! They need to give me a discount for this glowing review LOL.
Stopped in for lunch today and were shocked how much this place exceeded our expectations. The food was incredible. Will come back again and often!

I had to wait 15 minutes for my food it took a long time in all out what it was just chips the beer was nasty  water down I don't know what's going on but I'm not coming back the people are nice though
The waitress offered the daily special, but failed to mention that it was $17.  Beer Prices on Game Day are through the roof.  We won't be back.  It's a shame!!!!
Took waitress 10 minutes to greet us. Tried Dempsey's beer sampler - watery. Pizza was great.

Excellent service and very good food.  All beers brewed at Dempsey's are $3.50 on a normal night, and three nights each week they're down to $2.00.  Low prices at all times and amazing happy hour specials from 4 pm until 7 pm.  Let's support this new downtown business during the off-season.  Oh, and the fries taste like potatoes.  What more could you ask for?
Had a great lunch today great burger and crab cakes.. and the in house brew was wonderful The staff was the best, Thanks to all there for a great experience, I will return
